---

1 packet shredded coconut
1 pear
1 tin Pineapple Slices
20 g butter
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet cream
1 bunch mint
1 packet Meringue Nests

Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add the shredded coconut
and toast until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

Drain and finely chop the pineapple slices. Cut the pear into small chunks.
Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat. Cook the pineapple and pear
until lightly browned, 4-6 minutes. Add the butter and brown sugar and cook
until golden brown and sticky, 2-4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to
cool for at least 5 minutes.

In a large bowl, whisk the longlife cream until soft peaks form and almost
doubled in size, 3-4 minutes. Pick and thinly slice the mint leaves. Add 1/2 the
mint to the cream and gently stir to combine.
TIP: For the perfect soft peaks, whip until the cream just clings to the whisk or
beater when lifted.
TIP: If you don't have an electric beaters, use a hand metal whisk.

When you are ready to serve, dollop a spoonful of mint cream on each
meringue nest and top with the caramelised fruit. Sprinkle with the toasted
coconut and remaining mint.